@startuml
title Viaverse Security / Privacy / KVKK — Class Model

class AccountSession {
  id: UUID
  accountId: AccountId
  deviceId: UUID?
  refreshTokenHash: String
  ipHash: String
  userAgentHash: String
  status: SessionStatus
  expiresAt: Instant
  createdAt: Instant
}

class CapabilityGrant {
  accountId: AccountId
  capability: REQUEST_WORK | DO_WORK | OPERATE_BUSINESS
  status: GrantStatus
  verifiedAt: Instant?
  revokedAt: Instant?
}

class ConsentRecord {
  id: UUID
  accountId: AccountId
  purpose: ConsentPurpose
  status: GRANTED | DENIED | WITHDRAWN
  version: String
  source: String
  changedAt: Instant
}

class DataSubjectRequest {
  id: UUID
  accountId: AccountId
  requestType: EXPORT | DELETE | CORRECT
  status: DSARStatus
  verifiedAt: Instant?
  completedAt: Instant?
}

class SecurityPolicy {
  canAccessResource()
  canUseCapability()
  requiresAudit()
  requiresMfa()
  shouldRedactField()
  retentionForDataClass()
}

class DataClassification {
  dataClass: PUBLIC | INTERNAL | PERSONAL | SENSITIVE
  retentionClass: String
  encryptionRequired: Boolean
  auditRequired: Boolean
  exportable: Boolean
  deletable: Boolean
}

class SensitiveAccessAudit {
  id: UUID
  actorAccountId: AccountId
  resourceType: String
  resourceId: UUID
  action: String
  reason: String?
  correlationId: String
  createdAt: Instant
}

class SecurityPrivacyEvents {
  LoginSucceeded
  LoginFailed
  ConsentChanged
  DataExportReady
  DataDeleted
  SensitiveAccessLogged
  SecurityIncidentRaised
}

AccountSession --> CapabilityGrant : uses account
ConsentRecord --> DataSubjectRequest : affects
SecurityPolicy ..> CapabilityGrant : checks
SecurityPolicy --> DataClassification : uses
SecurityPolicy --> SensitiveAccessAudit : requires
DataSubjectRequest --> SensitiveAccessAudit : audits
ConsentRecord ..> SecurityPrivacyEvents : emits
DataSubjectRequest ..> SecurityPrivacyEvents : emits
SensitiveAccessAudit ..> SecurityPrivacyEvents : emits
AccountSession ..> SecurityPrivacyEvents : emits

note bottom
Account identity, capability grants and consent records are separate concepts.
Do not encode product capabilities as only string roles in JWT.
end note
@enduml
